                <p>Fitting of the dynamic <styled-content style="fixed-case">mRNA</styled-content> turnover model to experimental data. The two lower panels show the measured labeled <styled-content style="fixed-case">RNA</styled-content> (solid red line) and total <styled-content style="fixed-case">mRNA</styled-content> (solid black line) time courses for <styled-content style="fixed-case">YNL</styled-content>312<styled-content style="fixed-case">W</styled-content> (<styled-content style="fixed-case">RFA</styled-content>2). The time courses were fitted using either a variable degradation scenario (red/black dashed lines) or a constant degradation scenario (red/black dotted lines). In both scenarios, the synthesis rates are estimated by a piecewise linear function (first panel, dashed/dotted orange lines) and the degradation rates are estimated by a constant or a sine function (second panel, dashed/dotted blue lines), respectively.</p>
